John William Willis (31 August 1886 – 21 September 1963) was an English cricketer.  Willis was a right-handed batsman, though his bowling style is unknown.  He was born at Rothwell, Northamptonshire.
Willis made a single first-class appearance for Northamptonshire against Yorkshire in the 1919 County Championship.  In Northamptonshire's first-innings he was dismissed for 4 by Roy Kilner, while in their second-innings he was dismissed by the same bowler for a duck.  With the ball, Willis bowled a total of ten wicketless overs.He died at the town of his birth on 21 September 1963.
